<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold pb-8 pt-2">Ambitious Shit</h1>
<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
    <p class="text-white text-opacity-80 text-lg font-light">I came to SF to build Saas apps. I talked to a lot of people and they convinced me to pursure my other project - <a href="/myfriend" class="underline">MyFriend</a>.</p>
    <p class="text-white text-opacity-80 text-lg font-light">I already built an MVP of this project back in Czech Republic, so I started doing market research here in SF. I started going to senior facilities to talk to the future users to figure out their pain points and also get their opinions on the project. I also talked to the staff to figure out if they would use it as a monitoring device.</p>
    <p class="text-white text-opacity-80 text-lg font-light">I got some feedback, so I started talking to VCs and one VC told me the best advice I've ever gotten: "If you had unlimited time and unlimited resources, what would be the the craziest, most ambitious thing you would be working on in the next 5-10 years?"</p>
    <p class="text-white text-opacity-80 text-lg font-light">This question made me think totally differently. It made me realize that you could find the best problem to solve and make a ton of money out of it, but it may be something you don't want to do at all!</p>
    <p class="text-white text-opacity-80 text-lg font-light">So I stated thinking about the most ambitious shit that I could possibly do. I came up with a couple of ideas, one of them being a brain computer interface that allows you to control your computer and phone with your mind. Right now, we can read brain data. But what if we could write them? Then you could do insane stuff like googling only with using your brain. You could also inject stuff into the visual cortex, making embedded displays in your brain!!! You wouldn't even need the computer display or keyboard, you would just do everything with your mind!!!</p>
    <p class="text-white text-opacity-80 text-lg font-light">Contact me using the links below to see what's my progress on this!</p>

</div>